[{"id":"VH949941","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div>\n<div class=\"stimulus_reference\">\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure presents a diagram of two spheres and a point. Point P is shown above the midpoint between the two spheres. The first sphere has a positive charge of Q sub 1, and is located at a distance of d from Point P. The second sphere has a positive charge of Q sub 2 and is located at a horizontal distance from the first sphere, and at a distance of d from Point P.\" height=\"106\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VH949941.g02.png\" width=\"220\" /></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Point <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"P\"><math alttext=\"P\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>P</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> is a distance <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"d\"><math alttext=\"d\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>d</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> from each of two small charged spheres, as shown above. The first sphere has charge <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Q sub 1 equals Q\"><math alttext=\"Q sub 1 equals Q\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>Q</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mi>Q</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> , and the second sphere has charge <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Q sub 2 equals 2 Q\"><math alttext=\"Q sub 2 equals 2 Q\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>Q</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>Q</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> . The electric potential at point <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"P\"><math alttext=\"P\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>P</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> is <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"V\"><math alttext=\"V\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>V</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></spa